@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

@{b}Introduction@{ub}
@{b}============@{ub}

  I was looking for CD-Audio player which will be very small. Every that I found on AmiNet was using MUI, has too much options or simply doesn't work. So, I decided to write my own CD player.

  It has following features:

  - very small

  - easy to use

  - controlled by ARexx

  - compatible with MCDPlayer ID files

  - uses PopUp menus

  - works with scsi.device compatible cdroms

@endnode

@node USAGE "Usage"

@{b}Usage@{ub}
@{b}=====@{ub}

Place MiniCD where you want. I prefer WBStartup, because it will be hidden if you have no disc in CDROM, so it will not bother you.

You can set several program parameters in tooltypes and in command line:

  CX_PRIORITY=<number> - the priority of commodities hotkeys (default: 0)
  CX_POPKEY=<hotkey> - the key to pop up MiniCD window (default: control p)
  CX_POPUP=<bool> - open window at startup (only when disc is in CDROM) (default: YES)
  DEVICE=<device> - device name to which CDROM is connected (default: scsi.device)
  UNIT=<number> - device unit to which CDROM is connected (default: 1)
  SONGPATH=<path> - path to MCDP ID files (default: Songs)
  AUTOPLAY=<seconds> - automaticially starts playing CD after insert. <seconds> is a delay to wait before start playing. 0 seconds means no autoplaying (default: 0)
  AUTOEJECT - if this flag exists CD will eject when CD has finished (default: none)
  XPOS=<number> - x position of window (default: relative to screen width)
  YPOS=<number> - y position of window (default: 0)
  HEIGHTADD=<number> - add <number> pixels to window height. (default: 0)
  FONTNAME=<fontname> - name of font to use (must have '.font' extension in name) (default: screen font)
  FONTSIZE=<number> - size of font to use (default: screen font size)

@{b}Notes@{ub}
@{b}=====@{ub}

  When you remove disc from CDROM, MiniCD will hide. When you load CD, MiniCD will show up. When you will hide it manually it will stay hidden.
  MiniCD has various popup menus in various places. Over gadgets you have standard Project menu, over track number you have track releated functions and over time number you have time releated functions.

@endnode

@node WINDOWS "Windows"

@{b}Main window@{ub}
@{b}===========@{ub}

  >  - When stopped it starts playing CD from first track. When playing it skips to next track
  o  - Stop playing CD
  || - Pause CD
  @{u}^@{uu}  - Eject CD
       Hide - Hide MiniCD and stay hidden when CD was changed
       Quit - Quit from MiniCD

  00 - Current track
       Next track - go to next track
       Previous track - go to previous track
       Edit titles - Edit CD title names
       <track names> - List of tracks. Current track is rendered in bold font

  00:00 - Current time
       Title time - current track time
       Total time - time from the beginning of CD
       Remain title - time to end of track
       Remain disk - time to end of CD

  @{u}Shortcuts@{uu}
  > - fast forward
  < - fast rewind

@{b}Edit titles@{ub}
@{b}===========@{ub}

  Artist - Author of the CD
  Title - Title of the CD
  <names> - list of track names. To edit track name, click twice on track name (don't do doubleclick!)

@endnode

